<h1>Hello, World! Python Script<h1>
<p>This is a simple "Hello, World!" Python script that prints the text "Hello, World!" to the console.</p>

<h2>Running the script<h2>
<p>To run the script, open a terminal and navigate to the directory containing the script. Then, type the following command:</p>

<p>python hello_world.py</p>

<h2>Output</h2>
<p>The script will output the following text to the console:</p>

<p>Hello, World!</p>

<h2>equirements</h2>
<p>This script requires Python 3 to be installed on your machine. You can download Python 3 from the Python website.</p>

<p>I hope you find this script useful! Let me know if you have any questions or suggestions.</p>